{"version": 2, "width": 80, "height": 24, "timestamp": 1782434016, "idle_time_limit": 2.0, "env": {"SHELL": "/usr/bin/zsh", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}}
[0.004672, "o", "\u001b[36m# An AI agent connects to MCP servers. Each one hands it tools.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[36m# Which of those tools are a compliance problem?\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.507208, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 1: discover what the agent can actually do\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --discover mcp-config.json > my-agent.json\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.537941, "o", "\u001b[32m"]
[7.539971, "o", "# filesystem: discovered 14 tool(s)\r\n"]
[7.540399, "o", "\u001b[0m\u001b[90m# listed the live server's tools and classified each one. no hand-listing.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.542623, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m# Step 2: scan the deployment against the law, for Germany\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[90m$ agentic-compliance-scan --inventory my-agent.json --jurisdiction DE\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[10.802429, "o", "11 gap(s) found (high: 6, medium: 5).\r\n## National law (DE)\r\n### [high] Agent acts on an in-scope system with no risk analysis and information system security policies declared\r\n- Reference: NIS2 § 30 Abs. 2 Nr. 1 BSIG, DE BSIG (NIS2UmsuCG 2025)\r\n### [high] Agent acts on an in-scope system with no incident handling declared\r\n- Reference: NIS2 § 30 Abs. 2 Nr. 2 BSIG, DE BSIG (NIS2UmsuCG 2025)\r\n### [high] Agent acts on an in-scope system with no business continuity, backup and crisis management declared\r\n- Reference: NIS2 § 30 Abs. 2 Nr. 3 BSIG, DE BSIG (NIS2UmsuCG 2025)\r\n"]
[14.304468, "o", "\r\n\u001b[33m\u001b[1m# The point:\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[33m# 11 gaps, each cited to the actual German statute (BSIG), not the directive,\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[14.304537, "o", "\u001b[33m# ranked by real risk, from a real MCP server, in seconds.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[14.304831, "o", "\u001b[90m# github.com/cpoder/agentic-compliance-scan\u001b[0m\r\n"]
